  "label": "Simple Tomato Sauce",
  "notes": "Put the garlic and oil in a large skillet and sauté over medium heat until the garlic is pale gold. Add the tomatoes and basil. Season with salt and pepper and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until the oil begins to separate from the tomato.\n\nFresh tomatoes can be used if in they are season. Remove the skins and chop before using.\n\nVariations:\n\n- Sauté 1 small onion, 1 carrot, 1 stalk celery, 1 tablespoon parsley, all finely chopped, with the garlic.\n- Add a bay leaf, crushed chillies, anchovy fillet(s) or capers to the sauce when you add the tomatoes.",
